  "doc_id": "43011",
  "text": "An instrument's reliability assesses whether scores are stable and also determines whether observers rate the attribute or indicator consistently. In this evaluation multiple raters were used, but inter-reliability was not addressed. In future studies, consider using the same non-staff observer for all evaluations, and by doing so, the evaluator or researcher decreases the chances for measurement error by avoiding rater bias. [CITATION_1] ",
